Class DisplayStreamFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.support.v4.app.Fragment
      • edu.umich.globalchallenges.thirdeye.fragment.DisplayStreamFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.arch.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, android.arch.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnClickListener, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener

    public class DisplayStreamFragment
extends android.support.v4.app.Fragment
implements android.view.View.OnClickListener
    This fragment provides a view of the stream to the user. It also has a lot of controls for doing various things on the server (take pictures, video, etc.) but also has shortcuts to change some settings so the user doesn't have to leave the stream.
